NAME
    Eval::Util - Utilities related to eval()

VERSION
    This document describes version 0.001 of Eval::Util (from Perl
    distribution Eval-Util), released on 2018-03-05.

SYNOPSIS
     use Eval::Util qw(inside_eval);

     eval { say "foo" if inside_eval() };
     say "bar" if inside_eval();
     # will print C<foo> but not C<bar>.

DESCRIPTION
FUNCTIONS
    None exported by default, but they are exportable.

  inside_eval
    Usage: inside_eval() => bool

    Will check if running code is inside eval() (either string eval or block
    eval). This is done via examining the stack trace and checking for frame
    with subroutine named "(eval)".

